3.3.3. Lane switching

During lane switching, the controller needs to decide when to overtake a vehicle in the front and when to merge into another lane ( Fig. 4.18 ). In a traditional rule-based decision-making model, a single longitudinal and a lateral controller are combined with several manually defined criterions to make decisions on lane changing. Typical criterions [35] include safety criterion for deceleration caused to vehicles in the target lane: (4.17) a ˜ n ≥ − b safe where a ˜ n is the deceleration of the successor n and b safe is a given safe limit. This criterion avoids collision between the ego vehicle and the successor vehicle in the target lane.

